In patients known to be hypersensitive to amphetamine, or other components of Mixed Salts of a Single Entity Amphetamine Product. Hypersensitivity reactions such as angioedema and anaphylactic reactions have been reported in patients treated with other amphetamine products (seeÂ 

                        ADVERSE REACTIONS
                     ).

Serotonin syndrome, a potentially life-threatening reaction, may occur when amphetamines are used in combination with other drugs that affect the serotonergic neurotransmitter systems such as monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOIs), selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs), serotonin norepinephrine reuptake inhibitors (SNRIs), triptans, tricyclic antidepressants, fentanyl, lithium, tramadol, tryptophan, buspirone, and St. Johnâs Wort (see 

                              DRUG INTERACTIONS
                           ). The coadministration with cytochrome P450 (CYP2D6) inhibitors increase the risk with increased exposure to Mixed Salts of a Single Entity Amphetamine Product. In these situations, consider an alternative non-serotonergic drug or an alternative drug that does not inhibit CYP2D6 (see 

                              DRUG INTERACTIONS
                           ).

Concomitant use of Mixed Salts of a Single Entity Amphetamine Product with MAOI drugs is contraindicated (see 

                              CONTRAINDICATIONS
                           ).

Advise patients that there are potential risks to patients with serious cardiac disease, including sudden death, with Mixed Salts of a Single Entity Amphetamine Product use. Instruct patients to contact a healthcare provider immediately if they develop symptoms such as exertional chest pain, unexplained syncope, or other symptoms suggestive of cardiac disease (see 

                              WARNINGS
                           ).

Advise patients that Mixed Salts of a Single Entity Amphetamine Product can elevate blood pressure and heart rate (see 

                              WARNINGS
                           ).

Advise patients that Mixed Salts of a Single Entity Amphetamine Product, at recommended doses, can cause psychotic or manic symptoms, even in patients without prior history of psychotic symptoms or mania (see 

                              WARNINGS
                           ).

Advise patients that Mixed Salts of a Single Entity Amphetamine Product may cause slowing of growth including weight loss (see 

                              WARNINGS
                           ).

